          "text": "An 88-year-old woman with no significant medical history is brought to the emergency room by her daughter after a fall, where the woman lightly hit her head against a wall. The patient is lucid and complains of a mild headache. The daughter indicates that her mother did not lose consciousness after the fall. On exam, there are no focal neurological deficits, but you decide to perform a CT scan to be sure there is no intracranial bleeding. The CT scan are within normal limits and head MRI is preformed (shown). Which of the following conditions has the most similar risk factor to this patient's condition?",
