          "id": "medqa-e9dc0cd2d0b17441",
          "text": "A group of scientists is studying the mechanism by which the human papillomavirus (HPV) vaccine confers immunity. They observe that during the inoculation of test subjects, mammals with certain viral proteins result in the organism’s antigen-presenting cells (APCs) absorbing the antigen and presenting it on major histocompatibility complex (MHC) class 1 molecules. Which of the following is the correct term for the process that the scientists are observing in this inoculation?",
