          "text": "A 17-year-old girl with a BMI of 14.5 kg/m2 is admitted to the hospital for the treatment of anorexia nervosa. The patient is administered intravenous fluids and is supplied with 1,600 calories daily with an increase of 200 calories each day. On day 5 of treatment, the patient manifests symptoms of weakness and confusion, and dark brown urine. Which of the following clinical conditions is the most likely cause of the patient's symptoms?",
