          "id": "medqa-0c049be088c1be94",
          "text": "In a previous experiment infecting hepatocytes, it was shown that viable HDV virions were only produced in the presence of a co-infection with HBV. To better understand which HBV particle was necessary for the production of viable HDV virions, the scientist encoded in separate plasmids the various antigens/proteins of HBV and co-infected the hepatocytes with HDV. In which of the experiments would viable HDV virions be produced in conjunction with the appropriate HBV antigen/protein?",
