          "id": "medqa-5ee6bfca3b6e907e",
          "text": "A 45-year-old female with a history of gastroesophageal reflux disease presents to her family physician with symptoms of epigastric pain right after a meal. The physician performs a urea breath test which is positive and the patient is started on appropriate medical therapy. Three days later at a restaurant, she experienced severe flushing, tachycardia, hypotension, and vomiting after her first glass of wine. Which of the following is the mechanism of action of the medication causing this side effect?",
