          "id": "medqa-b3ed878079ce1ef4",
          "text": "A 15-year-old girl comes to the physician with her father for evaluation of short stature. She feels well overall but is concerned because all of her friends are taller than her. Her birth weight was normal. Menarche has not yet occurred. Her father says he also had short stature and late puberty. The girl is at the 5th percentile for height and 35th percentile for weight. Breast development is Tanner stage 2. Pubic and axillary hair is absent. An x-ray of the left hand and wrist shows a bone age of 12 years. Further evaluation of this patient is most likely to show which of the following sets of laboratory findings?\n $$$ FSH %%% LH %%% Estrogen %%% GnRH $$$",
