          "id": "medqa-264c82e345335cba",
          "text": "A 52-year-old woman comes to the emergency department because of epigastric abdominal pain that started after her last meal and has become progressively worse over the past 6 hours. She has had intermittent pain similar to this before, but it has never lasted this long. Her temperature is 39°C (102.2°F). Examination shows a soft abdomen with normal bowel sounds. The patient has sudden inspiratory arrest during right upper quadrant palpation. Her alkaline phosphatase, total bilirubin, amylase, and aspartate aminotransferase levels are within the reference ranges. Abdominal imaging is most likely to show which of the following findings?",
