          "id": "medqa-6ac6ab188e67ffd1",
          "text": "A study is conducted to find an association between serum cholesterol and ischemic heart disease. Data is collected, and patients are classified into either the \"high cholesterol\" or \"normal cholesterol\" group and also into groups whether or not the patient experiences stable angina. Which type of data analysis is most appropriate for this study?",
