          "id": "medqa-2f7cf0bb1a0b079c",
          "text": "A 45-year-old man presents with a long history of ulcers on the bottom of his feet. He recalls having a similar looking ulcer on the side of his penis when he was 19 years old for which he never sought treatment. The patient denies any fever, chills, or constitutional symptoms. He reports multiple sexual partners and a very promiscuous sexual history. He has also traveled extensively as a writer since he was 19. The patient is afebrile, and his vital signs are within normal limits. A rapid plasma reagin (RPR) test is positive, and the result of a Treponema pallidum particle agglutination (TP-PA) is pending. Which of the following findings would most likely be present in this patient?",
