          "id": "medqa-b01e0628519573cf",
          "text": "An investigator is comparing the risk of adverse effects among various antiarrhythmic medications. One of the drugs being studied primarily acts by blocking the outward flow of K+ during myocyte repolarization. Further investigation shows that the use of this drug is associated with a lower rate of ventricular tachycardia, ventricular fibrillation, and torsade de points when compared to similar drugs. Which of the following drugs is most likely being studied?",
