          "text": "A 25-year-old woman has dysuria, pyuria, increased frequency of urination, and fever of 1-day duration. She is sexually active. Urine cultures show gram-positive bacteria in clusters that are catalase-positive and coagulase-negative. The patient is started on trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole. Which of the following characteristics is used to identify the offending organism?",
