          "id": "medqa-4d62eb15ce96ead3",
          "text": "A 73-year-old female with no past medical history is hospitalized after she develops a fever associated with increasing shortness of breath. She states that 1 week prior, she had a cold which seemed to be resolving. Yesterday, however, she noticed that she started to feel feverish, measured her temperature to be 101.5°F (38.6°C), and also developed an unproductive dry cough and difficulty breathing. On exam, her temperature is 100.8°F (38.2°C), blood pressure is 110/72 mmHg, pulse is 96/min, and respirations are 16/min. Her exam demonstrates decreased breath sounds at the right lung base. The chest radiograph shows a right-sided pleural effusion with an opacity in the right lower lobe that is thought to be a bacterial pneumonia. Which of the following can be expected on a sample of the effusion fluid?",
