          "id": "medqa-8dab35447ab7d7e5",
          "text": "A 28-year-old man presents with a draining abscess on his left jaw. The patient states that he had a “bad tooth” a few weeks ago which has progressed to his current condition. His vital signs include: blood pressure 110/80 mm Hg, heart rate 85/min, and temperature 37.9°C (100.3°F). On physical examination, the patient has a 4 cm abscess on the left maxillary line that is draining a granulous, purulent material. Which of the following is the most likely causative organism of this abscess?",
