          "text": "A 39-year-old woman presents with progressive weakness, exercise intolerance, and occasional dizziness for the past 3 months. Past medical history is unremarkable. She reports an 18-pack-year smoking history and drinks alcohol rarely. Her vital signs include: temperature 36.6°C (97.8°F), blood pressure 139/82 mm Hg, pulse 98/min. Physical examination is unremarkable. Her laboratory results are significant for the following:\nHemoglobin 9.2 g/dL\nErythrocyte count 2.1 million/mm3\nMean corpuscular volume (MCV) 88 μm3\nMean corpuscular hemoglobin (MCH) 32 pg/cell\nLeukocyte count 7,500/mm3\nWhich of the following is the best next step in the management of this patient’s condition?",
