          "id": "medqa-5afdbb50bc02e3ce",
          "text": "A 42-year-old man comes to the physician because of a 3-week history of rash that began on his right ankle and gradually progressed up his calf. The rash is itchy and mildly painful. He has type 2 diabetes mellitus and hypertension. He does not smoke or drink alcohol. His current medications include metformin, glipizide, and enalapril. He returned from a trip to Nigeria around 5 weeks ago. He works on a fishing trawler. His temperature is 37°C (98.6°F), pulse is 65/min, and blood pressure is 150/86 mm Hg. Other than the rash on his calf, the examination shows no abnormalities. A picture of the rash is shown. Which of the following is the most likely cause of this patient's symptoms?",
